1. System Health

| Check          | Command       | Explanation                                |
| -------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Server uptime  | `uptime`      | Shows how long the server has been running |
| Last reboot    | `who -b`      | Confirms last boot time                    |
| Reboot history | `last reboot` | Detects unexpected restarts                |


2. CPU & Memory

| Check        | Command        | Explanation               |
| ------------ | -------------- | ------------------------- |
| CPU usage    | `top` / `htop` | Real-time CPU consumption |
| Memory usage | `free -h`      | RAM & swap usage          |
| Load average | `uptime`       | Checks CPU pressure       |
| VM stats     | `vmstat 1 5`   | CPU, memory, IO snapshot  |


3. Disk & Storage

| Check          | Command    | Explanation              |                 |
| -------------- | ---------- | ------------------------ | --------------- |
| Disk usage     | `df -h`    | Filesystem usage         |                 |
| Inode usage    | `df -i`    | Prevent inode exhaustion |                 |
| Directory size | `du -sh *` | Finds disk hogs          |                 |
| Block devices  | `lsblk`    | Shows disks & partitions |                 |
| Mounted FS     | `mount     | column -t`               | Verifies mounts |

4. Services & Processes

| Check               | Command                               | Explanation           |                        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------- | --------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Service status      | `systemctl status <svc>`              | Checks service health |                        |
| Running services    | `systemctl list-units --type=service` | Active services       |                        |
| High CPU process    | `ps aux --sort=-%cpu                  | head`                 | CPU-heavy processes    |
| High memory process | `ps aux --sort=-%mem                  | head`                 | Memory-heavy processes |

